<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Infra spec — {{MODULE_NAME}}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../research.css">
</head>
<!-- INFRA SPEC — the mini-SDD path, as a styled HTML artifact (same design system
     as the experiment card). Infrastructure tasks (pipelines, libraries, evaluation
     code, data loaders) are ordinary software and get ordinary software discipline:
     a short contract + acceptance tests BEFORE code, and tests must pass before the
     task is `done`. Use this instead of an experiment card when the work is plumbing,
     not a hypothesis test. If a task needs a traceability matrix, it belongs here,
     not on a card.
     Lives in a folder that has research.css/research.js one level up — e.g.
     specs/{{MODULE_SLUG}}/infra-spec.html, with a copy of research.css/research.js in
     specs/. Adjust the ../ paths if your layout differs (copy the assets next to it). -->
<body>
<div class="page-wrap">

  <nav class="sidebar" aria-label="Table of contents">
    <div class="sidebar-brand">
      <div class="sidebar-brand-name">{{PROJECT_SHORT_NAME}}
        <span>infra spec</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="sidebar-title">Contents</p>
    <div id="toc-list"></div>
  </nav>

  <div class="main-content">
    <header class="spec-header">
      <h1>Infra spec — {{MODULE_NAME}}</h1>
      <table class="meta-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Module</th>    <td><code>{{MODULE_PATH}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Status</th>    <td><span class="badge badge-draft">draft</span></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Author</th>    <td>{{AUTHOR}}</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Date</th>      <td>{{DATE}}</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Traces to</th> <td>{{PLAN_REF_OR_CARD_ID_OR_NONE}}</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <!-- Status badge: badge-draft → badge-ok (tests green, done) | badge-blocking
           (tests failing). Infrastructure is not `done` until acceptance tests pass. -->
    </header>

    <main>

      <section id="purpose">
        <h2>Purpose</h2>
        <p>{{ONE_PARAGRAPH_PURPOSE}}</p>
      </section>

      <section id="contract">
        <h2>Interface / contract</h2>
        <p>What this module exposes and guarantees — signatures, inputs/outputs,
           invariants, error behavior.</p>
        <pre><code>{{INTERFACE}}</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section id="acceptance-tests">
        <h2>Acceptance tests</h2>
        <p>Each row is a test that must pass before this task is
           <span class="badge badge-ok">done</span>.</p>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>ID</th><th>Given</th><th>When</th><th>Then</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>AT-1</code></td><td>{{GIVEN}}</td><td>{{WHEN}}</td><td>{{THEN}}</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Test command: <code>{{TEST_COMMAND}}</code>.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="dependencies">
        <h2>Dependencies</h2>
        <p>External libraries/APIs this touches: {{DEPENDENCIES_OR_NONE}}.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="out-of-scope">
        <h2>Out of scope</h2>
        <p>{{OUT_OF_SCOPE}}</p>
      </section>

      <section id="notes">
        <h2>Notes</h2>
        <div class="frozen-warning">
          <h4>Frozen-artifact note</h4>
          <p>Infrastructure that produces a <strong>frozen artifact</strong> (e.g. code
             that draws an eval split) still records its seed and config so the artifact
             is reproducible (<code>reference/reproducibility-policy.md</code>), and
             registers the output in the frozen manifest
             (<code>reference/frozen-artifacts-policy.md</code>).</p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="../research.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
